Republicans have retained their control of the Senate, and might extend their majority. In two of the year's most watched races, Ted Cruz defeated Beto O'Rourke in Texas and in Missouri, Josh Hawley beat Claire McCaskill.

Analysis From Our Reporters ›

Matt Flegenheimer

1576h ago
Remarkable on Florida: The swing-iest swing state on the presidential map, and a Dem hasn’t been elected governor since 1994.

Jeremy Peters

1576h ago
Trump is getting — and taking — a lot of credit for R victories. But Kris Kobach, a Trump ally considered for a cabinet job, lost big for Kansas gov.

Jeremy Peters

1576h ago
Alabama has voted to amend its constitution to allow Ten Commandments displays on public property. Roy Moore lives on.

Elizabeth Dias

1576h ago
As we wait for Georgia governor news: Exit polls show 89% of white evangelical voters supported Kemp.

Matt Flegenheimer

1576h ago
Major news in NY state politics: Dems take control of State Senate. Huge implications for liberal policymaking going forward.

Elizabeth Dias

1576h ago
An anti-abortion constitutional amendment passed in AL, and another is ahead in WV with 99% reporting. Both aim to challenge Roe in the Supreme Court.

Elizabeth Dias

1576h ago
Looking ahead: A 54 or 55 Republican majority in the Senate will make it harder for Democrats to win it back in 2020.

Jeremy Peters

1576h ago
Scott Walker has seen a lot of close, hard-fought races as Wisc. governor. This one might be his closest yet. Too close to call with 90% reporting.

Matt Flegenheimer

1576h ago
Definitely a rough night for Senate Dems, but the West is their place to play offense: AZ and NV, two pickup chances, still uncertain.

Astead Herndon

1576h ago
Wisconsin governor's race is close, but good news for Dems is that more than 40,000 votes are outstanding in Milwaukee. Should help Evers.

Jeremy Peters

1576h ago
Iowa is revealing its split political personality in a big way tonight. Dems pick up 2 House seats but can't keep Steve King from his 9th term.

Elizabeth Dias

1576h ago
In the midst of everything, don't forget Minnesota's hot race for AG — Keith Ellison just won, after allegations of abuse by an ex-girlfriend.

Nate Cohn

1576h ago
Our turnout estimate is 114 million votes cast in the House, breaking even our high expectations. Turnout in 2014 was 83 million.

Astead Herndon

1576h ago
The uncounted Milwaukee votes include 45,000 mailed and in-person ballots in the city, plus over 7,000 from Wauwatosa, Journal Sentinel reporting.

Matt Flegenheimer

1576h ago
Stacey Abrams just told a crowd in Georgia she's not conceding. Says she wants to see every vote counted.
